{
  "texts": [
    "Adapting a multimodal LLM to CXRs (CXR-LLaVA)A model influenced by the LLaVA network was developed [7].",
    "LLaVA, which consists of an LLM and an image encoder, converts images into a sequence of image tokens that are then combined with query text tokens for text generation within the LLM.",
    "Our primary objective was to fine-tune LLaVA using CXR-radiologic report pairs.To achieve optimal performance, we developed a custom image encoder from scratch rather than using pretrained weights.",
    "We empirically employed the \"ViT-L/16\" version of the vision transformer as the image encoder.",
    "This encoder begins with a convolutional layer that processes 1-channel grayscale CXR images into 1024dimensional patches."
  ]
}